2c86b0ef-e861-4d63-9abc-017c7e55da79.d393ef8b-5c05-4df3-8acd-b13cb6615224.description=
This flow wraps the RAS script aggr-get-iter.pl, which wraps the Ontap API method agg-get-iter.

Purpose\: get information about aggregates.

Possible inputs\:

clusterName\: this is mandatory(specifies the endpoint to run the api against)

aggregateName\: optional (Name of the aggregate.)
homeId\: optional  (NVRAM ID of the node to which this aggregate's disks have been administratively assigned)
homeName\: optional (Name of the node to which this aggregate's disks have been administratively assigned)
ownerId\: optional (NVRAM ID of node to which the aggregate ownership has been assigned. Normally, home-id matches owner-id. But these may be changed by SFO takeover to match the takeover node, and restored by SFO giveback to match home-id. CFO takeover and giveback do not affect owner-id.)
ownerName\: optional (Name of node to which the aggregate ownership has been assigned. Normally, home-name matches owner-name. But these may be changed by SFO takeover to match the takeover node, and restored by SFO giveback to match home-name. CFO takeover and giveback do not affect owner-name)
isHybrid\: optional (If true, aggregate currently contains both SSD and non-SSD RAID groups)
isHybridEnabled\: optional (If true, aggregate is eligible to contain both SSD and non-SSD RAID groups)
isInconsistent\: optional (Whether or not the aggregate is inconsistent. Default value is false.)
node\: optional (List of node names. If aggregate-name is also specified, then the matching aggregate on given nodes is returned. If not, all aggregates on specified nodes are returned. If this element is omitted when the request is sent to the Admin Vserver LIF, then all matching aggregates in the cluster are returned.)'

Optional inputs restrict the search, if none are given, all aggregates in the cluster are returned.

Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
2c86b0ef-e861-4d63-9abc-017c7e55da79.d69737bd-0c32-4319-a110-b4cf3281c98a.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

2c86b0ef-e861-4d63-9abc-017c7e55da79.description=
Synopsis

    This flow sets a cache configuration volume that contains a hybrid aggregate.
    setSusVolHybridCacheConfig performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the vServer based on he vServer name.
      2. Check that the vServer exists.
      3. Retrieve the volume details based on the volume name.
      4. Check that the volume exists.
      5. Retrieve the aggregates for the volume.
      6. Determine if the aggregate is a hybrid.
      7. If so, create a priority cache for the hybrid aggregate.
      8. Determine if the volume name is based on an ordinal number system. If not, rename the volume name to reflect an ordinal number system.
      9. Set the priority hybrid aggregate cache.
    10. Pass the information back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer used in the flow (required).
    volumeName - The volume name used in the flow (required).
    storageTier - The tier of storage (e.g. Vital, Velocity, or Value) (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS. 

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case a cache configuration for a hybrid aggregate on a volume.  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
